description: Rutgers Sikh Kirtan Night is a serene and uplifting evening hosted by the Sikh Student Association that brings the campus community together through the soulful singing of shabad kirtan, devotional hymns from the Guru Granth Sahib accompanied by traditional instruments like the harmonium and tabla. The event fosters an atmosphere of peace, reflection, and unity, allowing students and guests to de-stress while connecting spiritually. True to Sikh tradition, the night also includes Langar, a free communal meal that symbolizes equality and service. In addition, some gatherings feature cultural elements such as turban tying and interactive activities, making the event both spiritually enriching and culturally engaging. Open to people of all backgrounds, Kirtan Night offers a welcoming space to experience Sikh faith, music, and community on campus.
name: Rutgers Sikh Kirtan Night

description: Drop-in for an Artful Saturday monthly event hosted by the Center for the Women in the Arts at Douglass and Scarlet Arts RX! Kick off our Fall 2025 series with a beginner-friendly crafting session focused on cartoon-style self-portraits, vision boarding, and expressing yourself through drawing, collage, and mixed media! Artsy door prizes! Bring a friend! Taught by a Scarlet Arts Rx student teaching artist from Rutgers Mason Gross School of the Arts. Foundational art skills you will learn at this event: Cutting interesting shapes, Collage / mood boarding, and Cartoon self-portraits (out of the paper shapes). Free supplies, snacks, and boba provided! Supplies are limited – First come, first served. All skill levels and walk-ins welcome! This experience counts towards the Douglass Discovery curriculum requirement. description: Want to study abroad in Italy? We are offering an in-person information session (with free snacks!) at the Rutgers Global-Study Abroad conference room at 102 College Ave. The Director of Umbra Institute, Dr. Zach Nowak, will be joining us from Italy to answer any of your questions. It will start with a general presentation about studying abroad and the Umbra Institute, but most of the time will be allotted for questions and snacking. At Umbra, you can earn direct Rutgers credit for a wide range of fields, including:  Psychology Music, Fine Arts, & STEM Italian Language at any level (beginner to advanced) Food & Sustainability in the heart of the Mediterranean Innovative iCourses for intermediate Italian speakers—seminars in literature, media, and sociology taught in English with hour-long sections exclusively in Italian! Independent Research with distinguished faculty or direct enrollment at the Università di Perugia for advanced speakers  Explore Umbra’s full course catalog here. LEARN MORE AND APPLY HERE!
name: Study Abroad in Italy - Information Session

description: Join the BOLD Center at Douglass as we host our annual career conference! The Christiana Foglio DC'84 Douglass Career Conference is designed to empower students through career planning, discuss topics related to the workforce, and meet other professionals in a variety of industries to share their wealth of knowledge. Learn tips and tools for starting your career, how to navigate networking and interviewing, and the best ways to make your mark in the workplace. With a special focus on doing good work, we will also be hosting a packing party at the conference this year to donate items to community partners in need.  There will be food, giveaways, prizes, and networking opportunities.
name: Christiana Foglio DC'84 Douglass Career Conference

description: Stop by Douglass Library to experience a solo exhibition of artwork by the 2025-2026 Lebowitz Artist-in-Residence, Liz Collins, on view September 2 through March 13! Collins is a Brooklyn based artist that works across art and design. She is known for her innovative multimedia fabric, knitwear, and textile work, along with the fashion label she created. Don't miss out—RSVP today and join the Center for Women in the Arts at Douglass to view the exhibition during a reception and for a talk by artist Liz Collins on October 16, from 5:00 to 6:30 PM! All are welcome!Schedule: 5:00-5:30pm exhibition viewing & reception (light refreshments served); 5:30-6:30pm artist’s talk. This experience counts towards the Douglass Discovery curriculum requirement. R3: Career/Discovery/Professional Development/Research.Reminder: To receive DRC curriculum credit, you must complete a reflection survey.
location: Douglass Library: Mabel Smith Douglass Room & Mary H. Dana Women Artists Series Galleries

description: Join us for our annual 5K Run and Mile Walk! Whether you run, walk, volunteer, or cheer from the sidelines, help us raise awareness and support the fight against lung cancer. Interested in volunteering? Join our GroupMe!   The first 200 participants (walker or runner) will receive a free Wawa hot beverage coupon upon check-in!
